  "names": [
    {
      "full_name": "Research and Production Unitary Enterprise “Scientific and Technical Center ‘LEMT’ BelOMO”",
      "is_primary": true
    }
  ],
  "remarks": "The Belarusian Scientific and Technical Center “LEMT” is owned by the state enterprise BelOMO. LEMT manufactures optical sights and systems for conventional weapons, laser rangefinders, distance measurement modules based on diode lasers, and laser fire control systems. LEMT sights are used in the AK-12 automatic rifles produced by Russia’s Kalashnikov. Therefore, LEMT forms a part of the military and industrial complex of Belarus, including by being involved in the development and production of military technology and equipment.",
  "@context": "https://www.ammitto.org/ontology/context.jsonld"
}